Package org.kortforsyningen.proj

Java Native Interface for the PROJ C/C++ library. PROJ is a generic coordinate transformation software that transforms geospatial coordinates from one coordinate reference system (CRS) to another. This includes cartographic projections as well as geodetic transformations. This package exposes PROJ services as implementations of GeoAPI interfaces. Both PROJ 6 and GeoAPI are modeled according the ISO 19111 international standard. The use of GeoAPI interfaces allows developers to write their software in an implementation independent way, using the Proj class only as a starting point or for PROJ-specific actions.

This package requires installation of native libraries. The presence of those libraries can be tested as below:

 Proj.version().isPresent()

Coordinate operations can be performed as below. In this example, only the first line is PROJ-specific. All other lines should work in the same way with any GeoAPI implementations.

 CRSAuthorityFactory       factory   = Proj.getAuthorityFactory("EPSG");
 CoordinateReferenceSystem sourceCRS = factory.createCoordinateReferenceSystem("4326");   // WGS 84
 CoordinateReferenceSystem sourceCRS = factory.createCoordinateReferenceSystem("3395");   // WGS 84 / World Mercator
 // TODO: complete.

Unless otherwise noted in Javadoc, all classes in this package are safe for use in multi-thread environment. The main exception is WKTFormat.

    Static methods for coordinate reference systems and operations.

    Parses and format geodetic objects in Well Known Text format.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    GridAvailabilityUse
    Describes how grid availability is used.
    IntermediateCRSUse
    Describes if and how intermediate CRS should be used.
    SourceTargetCRSExtentUse
    Specifies how source and target CRS extents should be used to restrict candidate operations.
    SpatialCriterion
    Spatial criterion to restrict candidate operations.
    WKTFormat.Convention
    Controls some aspects in formatting of geodetic objects as Well Known Text.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    FormattingException
    Thrown when a PROJ object can not be parsed from or formatted to Well Known Text.
